English:  Extinctbirds1907 P42, The giant moa (Dinornis novaezealandiae) is an extinct genus of ratite birds belonging to the moa family. It was endemic to New Zealand. In Rothschild's book 'Extinct Birds' this moa has been given the scientific name Dinornis ingens.

One-Eleventh Natural Size—restoration from skeleton and feathers
